What you need to know:

The Brewers still lead the standings on 26 points from 11 matches after a hard-fought 1-0 victory over Wazito on Friday but have played one game more than bankersIn another match played at the same venue, William Wadri scored as Bandari registered their first win against Nairobi-based teams by beating Kariobangi Sharks 1-0At Bukhungu stadium, Shami Kibwana scored for Kakamega Homeboyz in 73rd minute while David Okoth added the second in the 90th minute to sink newly promoted Nairobi City Stars 2-0